The paper proposes a novel framework for session-based recommendation using recurrent neural networks and attentional networks. The paper discusses the importance of temporal dynamics in recommendation systems and proposes a method to incorporate long-term user interactions across sessions. This work involves deep learning, natural language processing, and information retrieval techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.CR.
